        <briefdescription>
<para>Returns the ordered operation sequence for a single job as typed value tuples. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Zips <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_data_1_1_taillard_instance_1a9ee0366b1709a54f08fb45a32e4fb0e9" kindref="member">machines_matrix</ref> and <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_data_1_1_taillard_instance_1a7590980360c981cb8e7a63498bb96f77" kindref="member">duration_matrix</ref> for the given job index into an array of <computeroutput></computeroutput>(machine, duration) pairs in operation order. This is the primary data accessor used by DESSimulator.LoadInstance when constructing Operation objects.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>jobIndex</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Zero-based index of the job to query. Must be in the range <computeroutput></computeroutput>[0, JobCount).</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>An array of <computeroutput></computeroutput>(int machine, int duration) tuples, one per operation, in the order they must be executed. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
